		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">It could work. You'd need to start small, though. You'd probably want to work the strategy around my level, with each druid kiting one or two. </P><P>Actually, with a full group, I would only have 4 of the druids kiting. Have one to heal incase kiting goes bad for someone, then one to direct the traffic and keep group together so that xp is shared. This one can also AoE mobs that are in same proxemity. </P><P>Take, say, the big 'bold camp in Stonebrunt. You can get 8 spawns easily at one time. The group leader goes through and casts harmony on the whole camp, then points out the two mobs that the first druid will snare. Then the 2nd. etc. You have to do this in pull order, otherwise a druid is going to over-pull on thier kiting. </P><P>Run together. Leader casts AoE. The healer heals if someone gets in trouble, and also charms any animals that wander up. Leader handles any non-animal adds.</P><P>I think the worst part would be lag issues from all the casting. But I think it would be awesome to try. Hm..I think my guild has enough druids of similar level we might can try this...<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
