		<hr size="1">Tried it folks, it doesnt work very well. For one, pulling quad spawns for six people, having them all pull, and still keeping everyone close enough to get exp (notice if you walk too far from your group you get no exp) It would have to be done in an increadibly wide open area, with enough mobs for everyone to pull some, and yet not too much to get too many adds. Then you would have to all pull close and kill near eachother, which has only been done successfully a couple times. I have gotten okay exp from trying it with buddies, but the number of goof-ups, missed exp, and bad pulls made it so soloing while quad kiting is easier and more efficient. <BR>Nice idea though, but this works better:</P><P> if you kept the pulls down to one or two, and didnt have the whole group pull, and you pulled circles around the ones that were medding/healing so they get exp (tried that too) it works alot easier than all pulling in different directions. Then, when you are oom, you take a med break while the others fill in and take your place.</P><P>  -K</P><P><center><table style="filter: glow(color=blue, Strength=6)"><font color=firebrick size="2"><b><BR>"Gravity Isn't so much a law as it is a good idea" </b></font></table></P><P></P><P>For the best Druid info on the net-<BR><a href="http://www.eqdruids.com">Visit EQ Druids.com</a><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
