		<hr size="1">This is the kind of ideas people come up with when they're lvl 16...</P><P><BR>Anyway, what really could work, is going to a place like Jagged Pine and having a few druids in the group charm some good animals. Griffons would be the best, cuz they're tough and gritty and they typically charm for a good few minutes. Then, with these uber pets, go take some of the camps in there that require groups. You could do the potomaids, etc. Have at least one druid in the group w/none charmed to be ready to save the group from 4 or 5 griffons and a bunch of potemaids lol. Make sure everything (except the maids, that is, for obvious reasons---they can't be) snared. </P><P>Silly ideas like these would work, but aren't going to be overly efficient. I highly doubt they would get as much exp as me w/one animal charmed. Or, me quadding. However, if there were a group of friends on that all played druids or chanters, and there were no real tanks available...and a zone happened to have decent animals to charm (or things to charm w/chanters)...then if there was a specific camp someone needed to take they could be able to do it. IF they needed a quest peice, something dropped there frequently...who knows. Charmed pets are certainly uber (I took a whole tent of poachers in JP w/one snake. I only hasted it w/savage, DSd it and healed it twice. It got a little interesting w/the charm wore, but i recharmed and then ate the snake hehe). </P><P>Silly ideas like that, and the multi quad one, can certainly get you killed. That's for sure. So, unless you're desperate or in the mood to be silly, I suggest quadding on your own and doing things the old fashion way---whether grouping or solo ing. Even w/the knew group bonus. <br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
